olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
½ sachet dried oregano
2 clove garlic
1 packet beef mince
1 egg
½ packet fine breadcrumbs
1 packet salad leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 apple

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut the potato into bite-sized chunks. Slice the carrot into thick rounds. Place the potato and carrot on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, then add the dried oregano (see ingredients) and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat and roast until tender 20-25 minutes.

Finely chop the garlic. In a large bowl, combine the beef mince, garlic, Louisiana spice blend, egg, grated Parmesan cheese and fine breadcrumbs (see ingredients). Season with pepper and mix well.

Using damp hands, form heaped spoonfuls of the beef mixture into meatballs, then flatten to make 1cm-thick rissoles. Transfer to a plate. You should get 3-4 rissoles per person.

Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the rissoles, in batches, until browned all over and cooked through, 4-5 minutes each side.

While the rissoles are cooking, thinly slice the apple. In a second large bowl, combine the apple and mixed salad leaves. Add a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil and toss to coat. Season to taste.

Divide the cheesy beef rissoles and roasted veggie chunks between plates. Spoon the smokey aioli over the rissoles and serve with the apple salad.